  other examples of offenbach 's use of incongruity are noted by the critic paul taylor : " in la belle hélène , the kings of greece denounce paris as ' un vil séducteur ' to a waltz tempo that is itself unsuitably seductive … the potty - sounding phrase ' l'homme à la pomme ' becomes the absurd nucleus of a big cod - ensemble."taylor , paul .

